  "body": "## Problem\r\nToday is September 16. UI jumps from `Yesterday` to `September 14` in the #desktop channel.\r\n\r\n- There were messages, they show on mobile\r\n- 3 messages send in the evening (20:29, 21:15, 21:45 PM CEST) are visible\r\n- Yesterday's messages in #weather are visible\r\n- I sent a message to both channels \r\n- In #desktop I also sent a reply\r\n- I noticed an error window when returning to my laptop at some point. Could Select OK and continue using the app. It didn't crash, unfortunately didn't take a screenshot.\r\n\r\n### Current\r\n\r\n- No messages from yesterday in a specific channel\r\n- No option to fetch messages manually (#3368) \r\n\r\n### Expected\r\n- Yesterday's messages are complete. Behavior to accomplish depends on bug. Maybe the app could attempt fetching messages of the last x days again if an error is logged?\r\n- Option to fetch messages manually (#3368) \r\n\r\n\r\n",
